13:06.620 --> 13:08.622
- with traces of churned goat's milk!
- So cheese!

13:08.688 --> 13:10.361
Ew, I need a bucket!

13:10.423 --> 13:12.733
Ladies, we have a guest.

13:12.793 --> 13:14.363
I am- I'm really sorry about this.

13:14.427 --> 13:16.407
I'm just at my wit's end with these two.

13:16.463 --> 13:18.500
I don't suppose you have
any experience with teenagers?

13:18.565 --> 13:19.908
Oh, no.

13:19.966 --> 13:21.877
You two remind me of me and my sister.

13:21.935 --> 13:23.573
We used to fight all the time.

13:23.637 --> 13:25.674
I used to accuse her
of stealing my boyfriends.

13:25.739 --> 13:27.741
She would accuse me of trying to stab her.

13:27.808 --> 13:29.879
- You know, sister stuff.
- Oh, my God.

13:29.943 --> 13:34.187
Trust me, if I wanted to stab her,
that skank be stabbed.

13:35.549 --> 13:37.722
She's not a therapist, is she?

13:38.718 --> 13:39.719
Just-

13:39.786 --> 13:41.390
I didn't sleep a wink.

13:41.454 --> 13:43.456
I-i cannot stop thinking about Ronaldo.

13:43.523 --> 13:47.061
I know. I dreamt our wedding
made the cover of Modern Gay Grooms...

13:47.127 --> 13:49.300
and that there was
a magazine called Modern Gay Grooms.

13:49.362 --> 13:52.206
Okay, that's- that's Pepper.

13:52.265 --> 13:54.575
Let's just ask him
to let Ronaldo take the lead.

13:54.634 --> 13:56.136
And risk hurting Pepper?

13:56.203 --> 13:59.514
For all we know, Ronaldo hasn't
even given us a second thought.

13:59.573 --> 14:01.814
I couldn't stop thinking about you.

14:01.875 --> 14:03.786
What happened here yesterday was real.

14:03.844 --> 14:05.881
Oh, Ronaldo, we felt it too.

14:05.946 --> 14:07.755
- But what about Pepper?
- I left him.

14:07.814 --> 14:09.293
- What?
- It's over.

14:09.349 --> 14:11.226
He doesn't look at me the way you do.

14:11.284 --> 14:13.457
Oh, this is all happening so fast.

14:13.520 --> 14:17.024
For me too.
But my heart was racing when I left here.

14:17.090 --> 14:18.797
You are my muses-es.

14:18.859 --> 14:21.135
Oh, I feel so guilty.

14:21.194 --> 14:23.367
One quick look. No one has to know.

14:24.664 --> 14:25.836
Oh.

14:25.899 --> 14:27.845
Oh, Ronaldo, what have you done?

14:27.901 --> 14:29.881
Mitchell! Cameron!

14:29.936 --> 14:31.643
- Oh, no!
- Quick! Hide!

14:31.705 --> 14:32.945
Yeah, yeah, yeah! I'll hide.

14:33.006 --> 14:35.213
- Cam, not you.
- Okay, yeah. Go, go, go, go, go.

14:36.776 --> 14:38.312
Ronaldo left me.

14:38.378 --> 14:39.413
- What?
- No!

14:39.479 --> 14:40.787
- The swine.
- Oh!

14:40.847 --> 14:43.589
Someone put it in his head that
he could do this without me.

14:43.650 --> 14:45.687
But mark my words, I will destroy him...

14:45.752 --> 14:47.629
and whatever wedding
he thinks he's planning.

14:47.687 --> 14:49.189
Okay, well, that's one way to go.

14:50.323 --> 14:52.303
Daddies, there's a man in the bathroom.

14:52.359 --> 14:53.667
What?

14:53.727 --> 14:55.138
- That's a Wiggles song.
- It's a Wiggles song.

14:55.195 --> 14:57.698
♪ Daddy, there's a man
in the bathroom ♪

14:57.764 --> 14:59.072
♪ There's a man in the ♪

14:59.132 --> 15:01.009
- It's okay, honey. it's okay.
- ♪ He's in the shower ♪

15:01.067 --> 15:02.671
Ronaldo was nothing before I found him...

15:02.736 --> 15:05.842
living in squalor in a dump
barely bigger than this.

15:05.906 --> 15:07.783
How could he do this to me?

15:07.841 --> 15:10.117
Because you never listen to anybody.

15:10.176 --> 15:13.680
I have good ideas,
but you're too thick-headed to hear them.

15:13.747 --> 15:15.852
Ronaldo, how did you get here?

15:15.916 --> 15:18.396
It was you two.

15:18.451 --> 15:21.022
You plotted against me.

15:21.087 --> 15:23.624
I bet that's not even
a Wiggles song, is it?

15:23.690 --> 15:25.067
- Is it?
- No.

15:25.125 --> 15:28.368
- Oh.
- Pepper, we can explain.

15:29.963 --> 15:31.499
Oh.

15:31.564 --> 15:33.544
Do you have any idea how hard I work?

15:33.600 --> 15:35.841
Well, maybe that's part of the problem.

15:35.902 --> 15:38.348
I mean, you've been
through the mill, Pepper.

15:38.405 --> 15:39.713
Heard it.

15:39.773 --> 15:43.653
I've done 53 gay weddings, and-

15:46.379 --> 15:48.757
And... none of them are mine.

15:48.815 --> 15:49.816
- Oh.
- Pepper.

15:49.883 --> 15:52.090
And whose fault is that?

15:52.152 --> 15:55.326
I feel like you're implying mine,
but I really don't see it.

15:55.388 --> 16:00.337
How can a man with such flair for setting tables
leave no seat for one who loves him?

16:00.393 --> 16:02.464
- Oh, my God.
- Ronaldo's in love with Pepper.

16:02.529 --> 16:04.167
I know.
That's why I said, "Oh, my God."

16:04.230 --> 16:06.267
Pepper, do you hear
what Ronaldo is saying?

16:06.333 --> 16:08.472
Of course I do. I'm not a fool.

16:08.535 --> 16:10.037
He thinks I can't set a table.

16:10.103 --> 16:13.676
No, no, no.
Ronaldo is in love with you. Go to him.

16:13.740 --> 16:15.344
What?

16:17.143 --> 16:18.349
You're in love with me?

16:18.411 --> 16:19.719
Sí.

16:19.779 --> 16:21.725
It is true. Yes.

16:21.781 --> 16:23.727
God, that would drive me crazy.

16:23.783 --> 16:27.287
Ronaldo, I- I don't know what to say.

16:27.354 --> 16:30.824
I mean, of course when I hired you,
I found you very attractive.

16:30.890 --> 16:32.563
That's why I hire all my people.

16:34.127 --> 16:36.403
But I-

16:36.463 --> 16:40.605
I never thought you... would find me-

16:40.667 --> 16:42.578
¿Perfecto?

16:43.803 --> 16:46.079
Because that's what you are- perfect.

16:46.139 --> 16:48.813
No, I'm out. I'm out. I'm out. I can't.

16:53.613 --> 16:56.287
Gloria, I forgot my towel!

16:56.349 --> 16:59.125
Here it is.
Nice and toasty from the dryer.

17:00.453 --> 17:01.693
Gloria!

17:01.755 --> 17:03.792
She ran to the store. Breakfast in five.

17:03.857 --> 17:05.962
Your underpants are pressed
and on your bed.

17:07.660 --> 17:08.730
Gloria!

17:08.795 --> 17:10.172
So if I'm hearing you right...

17:10.230 --> 17:12.436
you're not so much mad
about the prostitute in the kitchen...

17:12.499 --> 17:14.103
as you are about my lying to you.

17:14.166 --> 17:15.771
No, I'm mad about the prostitute
in the kitchen.

17:15.835 --> 17:17.108
- Mm.
- That's my bad.

17:17.170 --> 17:19.172
Yes, it is.
It's your bad, Frank. Very bad.

17:19.239 --> 17:21.480
Look, I'm a progressive woman.

17:21.540 --> 17:23.316
I-i took a pole dancing class.

17:23.376 --> 17:25.413
I sent my daughter to college
with condoms.

17:25.478 --> 17:27.458
Now I think that sends the wrong message.

17:27.513 --> 17:29.551
- Thank you very much.
- No, you don't get to judge!

17:29.616 --> 17:32.062
Frank, I'm-

17:32.118 --> 17:35.463
I know you're upset
about Annie breaking up with you.

17:35.522 --> 17:38.025
Wait, Annie didn't break up with me.

17:38.091 --> 17:39.297
I broke up with her.

17:39.359 --> 17:41.771
- What?
- Why? I thought she was so great!

17:41.828 --> 17:44.240
Well, I got scared.

17:44.297 --> 17:47.710
I didn't know how to...
be with another woman.

17:47.767 --> 17:49.678
I thought your mother and I
would be together forever.

17:49.736 --> 17:51.215
- Ah-
- I'm sorry, Dad.

17:51.271 --> 17:53.774
I never would have
gone through with it last night...

17:53.840 --> 17:57.617
but, uh, Jeannie was so nice
and professional.

17:57.677 --> 17:59.452
Thank you, Frank.

17:59.512 --> 18:03.085
And for what it's worth,
you got nothing to be nervous about.

18:03.149 --> 18:06.062
- You were wonderful.
- Really? You think so?

18:06.119 --> 18:07.291
Yeah.

18:07.353 --> 18:09.993
If you love that woman,
you should go get her back.

18:10.056 --> 18:11.228
She'd be lucky to have you.

18:11.291 --> 18:12.497
Oh.

18:12.559 --> 18:14.334
Seriously. I see a lot of guys your age.

18:14.394 --> 18:17.238
- Most of them can barely-
- Okay. Let's get you in that cab.

18:17.297 --> 18:18.708
I love your kids.

18:18.765 --> 18:21.211
- That Alex is like a little me.
- Oh, my God.

18:23.336 --> 18:25.577
Good morning, boss, junior boss.

18:25.638 --> 18:27.549
Grab a seat and check it out.

18:27.607 --> 18:29.951
Egg white omelet,
high-protein smoothies...

18:30.009 --> 18:31.886
then I thought we could put on
our running shoes-

18:31.945 --> 18:33.947
I need to cut you off right there, chief.

18:34.013 --> 18:35.993
Seems my wife overstepped her bounds.

18:36.049 --> 18:38.029
Now, you seem like a nice guy.

18:38.084 --> 18:41.088
- Thanks.
- But I don't think you're the best fit for this house.

18:41.154 --> 18:42.690
Are- Are you serious?

18:42.755 --> 18:45.395
- I'm afraid so.
- Okay.

18:45.458 --> 18:47.870
- It was the underpants, wasn't it?
- That didn't help.

18:47.927 --> 18:50.305
Man, I came on too strong. Gosh dang it!

18:50.363 --> 18:52.502
My dad warned me about that
when I turned 14.

18:52.565 --> 18:55.375
He said, "Son, you're about to be
the man of the family.

18:55.435 --> 18:57.779
You got to learn to give people time
to see how special you are."

18:57.837 --> 19:00.078
- Why were you the man of the family?
- Uh-

19:00.140 --> 19:01.881
- He sort of died.
- How?

19:01.941 --> 19:03.943
I don't wanna bring you down, little man.

19:04.010 --> 19:05.580
Neither did my dad.

19:05.645 --> 19:09.092
He'd say, "My disease can't be all bad
if it rhymes with 'answer."'

19:10.617 --> 19:13.097
Those are the flaxseed muffins
that I just baked.

19:13.153 --> 19:15.793
I'll just take 'em out
and get out of here.

19:15.855 --> 19:16.890
Andy, wait.

19:18.158 --> 19:19.899
We're never gonna eat 'em.

19:19.959 --> 19:23.202
Well, then. I'm sorry it didn't work out.

19:23.263 --> 19:25.709
- What didn't work out?
- My mission here.

19:25.765 --> 19:28.644
It was really nice
to meet you though, Mrs. P.

19:28.701 --> 19:31.204
You didn't even give him a chance.

19:31.271 --> 19:33.444
- We took a vote, Mom.
- You gotta respect the vote.

19:33.506 --> 19:36.146
No! You make me hire these nannies
that I don't like.

19:36.209 --> 19:38.780
But when I find one
that I like, you fire him?

19:38.845 --> 19:43.453
I am the one that spends most of the time
around here, so I get to pick!

19:43.516 --> 19:48.659
Shh. Sometimes the louder we are,
the less we're heard.

19:48.721 --> 19:51.292
- You're frustrated right now, aren't you?
- Yes.

19:51.357 --> 19:54.304
Because you feel
like they're not hearing you.

19:54.360 --> 19:56.465
Yes.

19:56.529 --> 19:58.065
Well, that's exactly how they feel.

20:00.934 --> 20:03.505
I'm sorry that I ignored your feelings.

20:05.104 --> 20:07.846
I promise that I will try
not to yell so much.

20:07.907 --> 20:09.386
You're hired.

20:09.442 --> 20:11.422
- What?
- You'd better drink that smoothie.

20:11.477 --> 20:14.253
- We're going on a run!
- This isn't over.

20:15.949 --> 20:17.428
Life isn't easy.

20:17.483 --> 20:19.963
Sometimes we just need a little help-

20:20.019 --> 20:22.295
Getting your confidence back.

20:22.355 --> 20:25.768
Getting on the same page.

20:25.825 --> 20:27.395
Getting out of your own way.

20:33.366 --> 20:35.505
Or just getting moving.

20:35.568 --> 20:37.479
And I'm pleased as punch to be the one-

20:37.537 --> 20:40.040
Okay, this is tough enough
without all the yammering!

20:40.106 --> 20:41.779
Sorry.

20:41.841 --> 20:42.979
Whoo!

20:46.145 --> 20:47.419
What would you like to dance to?

20:47.480 --> 20:48.754
I have to tell you...

20:48.815 --> 20:50.488
we have to have
some sort of square dancing.

20:50.550 --> 20:52.120
We're not doing country.

20:52.185 --> 20:55.655
No square dancing.
There will be no hoedown tonight.

20:55.722 --> 20:58.202
My family is going
to throw a fit. They're gonna riot.

20:58.258 --> 21:00.465
We're not getting married
for them. We're getting married for us.

21:00.526 --> 21:02.267
I think we have
a decorative cake out front...

21:02.328 --> 21:03.807
then we have sheet cakes in the back.

21:03.863 --> 21:07.072
Oh, I see.
Is that the theme you're going for- tacky?

21:07.133 --> 21:08.339
"Sheet," like a sheet.

21:08.401 --> 21:10.176
Oh, "sheet."
I thought he said "chic cake."

21:10.236 --> 21:13.080
- Pepper!
- All of my cakes are chic.

21:13.139 --> 21:15.016
Oh, they are, yeah!
